com.google.thingbrowser.modules.slideshow.view.play
Class PlayingMovieInterpolationModel

java.lang.Object
  com.google.thingbrowser.modules.slideshow.view.play.PlayingMovieInterpolationModel

public class PlayingMovieInterpolationModel
extends java.lang.Object

A PlayingMovieModel is an optimized data structure supporting [near] realtime playback of a slideshow "movie". Some client sets up the model by adding successive "intervals" of visual and sound track information, The player can then set the current time (relative to the starting point) and query for what the state should be at that time. The PlayingMovieModel takes care of interpolating as necessary, allowing the player to choose its preferred frame rate independently.

This class does not fire any propertyChange events. The client is responsible for querying the state as needed.

appendVisualInterval

public void appendVisualInterval(double duration,
                                 java.awt.Image image,
                                 java.awt.geom.AffineTransform start,
                                 java.awt.geom.AffineTransform end)
Append an interval of visual animation of an image. The image is to be animated (interpolated) between a starting and ending transform.

Parameters:
duration - the duration of the interval.
image - the image to animate.
start - the starting transform for the image.
end - the ending transform for the image.

appendSoundInterval

public void appendSoundInterval(double duration,
                                Player sound)
Append an interval of sound playback. The sound is to be played for the specified duration, then stopped. If the supplied Player contains a sound clip shorter than the desired duration, the remainder of the duration will be filled with silence.

Parameters:
duration - the duration of the interval.
sound - a Player that can play the desired sound.

Get the currently active image, based on the current time. Returns null if there is no active visual interval at the current time.

getCurrentTransform

public java.awt.geom.AffineTransform getCurrentTransform()
Get the currently active transform, based on the current time. Returns an identity transform if there is no active visual interval at the current time.

The returned object is a pointer to internal state; the client should not modify it.

See Also:
setCurrentTime(double)

getCurrentSound

public Player getCurrentSound()
Get the currently active sound clip, based on the current time. Returns null if there is no active sound interval at the current time.

The client is responsible for calling play() or stop() on the returned objects as needed.
